NUMBER 1904
NAME The Aquarium
INDOOR_FLOOR
FIXED_LIGHT
REGION 0
;
;
;chair
ITEM 0 86
;
;table
ITEM 1 91
;
;portrait
ITEM 2 1308
;
;curtain
ITEM 3 1031
;
*DESCRIPTION_START
Sand and colorful gravel cover the floor in Thresher's aquarium. Small tropical
fish dart this way and that. A huge coral reef is home to several other
species of life. A huge oyster has been crafted into the shape of a chair,
while the bones of one of Threshers meals has been turned into a table. A 
portrait of Thresher standing proudly next to a man strung up on a fish
scale hangs on the reef.
*DESCRIPTION_END
;
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAM 0
The pink shell of an oyster has been carefully crafted into the shape of a
chair. Several remorra fish wait patiently by it for Thresher to sit and
relax.
*DESCRIPTION_END
;
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAM 1
Bleached white bones of a huge fish form the shape of a table. Huge teeth
marks on the bones make it pretty obvious this used to be Threshers dinner
at one time.
*DESCRIPTION_END
;
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAM 2
Beaming proudly at his catch, Thresher stands next to a man strung up on a 
fish scale at some local dock. Scrawled on the picture are the words,
"Dinner - Olum 19, 1040, off the coast of Crescent Isle, 235 pounds"
*DESCRIPTION_END
;
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAM 3
A dark curtain hangs completely around the aquarium, ready to close off
the glass walls from prying eyes.
*DESCRIPTION_END
;IFPREVERB EXAM 3
;  IFVAR ITEMVAL3 = 1
;    CLEARVERB
;    SHOWROOM 1315
;  ENDIF
;ENDIF
;
IFPREVERB PULL 3
  IFVAR ITEMVAL3 = 0
    CLEARVERB
    ECHO PLAYER You pull the curtains open, letting in the outside light.
    ECHO OTHERS %n pulls the curtain open, the light shining through the glass walls of the aquarium.
    EQUAL ITEMVAL3 1
;    AFFECT 1315
;    SETITEMVAL 0 3 1
;    ECHO ALL The curtains to the aquarium open, adding a watery landscape to the room.
;    AFFECT 1904
   ELSE
    ECHO PLAYER The curtains are already open.
  ENDIF  
ENDIF
;
IFPREVERB PUSH 3
  IFVAR ITEMVAL3 = 1
    CLEARVERB
    ECHO PLAYER You close the curtains, shielding the room from prying eyes.
    ECHO OTHERS %n closes the curtains
    EQUAL ITEMVAL3 0
;    AFFECT 1315
;    SETITEMVAL 0 3 0
;    ECHO ALL The curtains around the aquarium draw closed.
;    AFFECT 1904
  ELSE
    ECHO PLAYER The curtains are already closed.
ENDIF
;
NUMBER 1905
NAME Dark Of Night
DEEPCAVE
PARTIAL_DARKNESS
REGION 0
CALL 33
EXIT U 229
EXIT D 206
;altar
ITEM 0 236 ADJ1=25 ADJ2=218
EXTEND 0 with intricate silver runes on the sides.
*DESCRIPTION_START
You are enveloped in darkness like you have never felt before. This immense cavern seems to shift continually as if it were constructed out of the night itself. Glimpses of light can be seen occasionally from all different directions. You can make out the presence of a large altar near the center of the room.
*DESCRIPTION_END

*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAM 0
The altar rises out of the ground in the center of this dark cavern as
if it has taken root and grown there. Cracks and crevices in its surface
provide some insight as to how it has been used.
*DESCRIPTION_END
;
IFPREVERB KISS 0
CLEARVERB
ECHO PLAYER Your affection to the night brings about a feeling of peace and refreshment.
ECHO OTHERS %n is wrapped in the comfort of the night looking invigorated.
SPELL 347 50
SPELL 343 50
SPELL 303 50 
SPELL 319 50
SPELL 515 50
ADD BODYPOINTS 250
ENDIF
;
IFPREVERB GO 0
CLEARVERB
ECHO PLAYER Just as you lay your body onto the altar you begin to feel sleepy.
ECHO OTHERS As %n leans back onto the altar he begins to fall asleep.
SPELL 218 100
DAMAGEPLR SLASH 150 A sacrificial blade appears above you and plunges into your chest.
ECHO OTHERS A sacrificial blade appears above %n and plunges into %h chest.
POSITION LAY
ENDIF
;
IFPREVERB LISTEN -1
   CLEARVERB
   ECHO PLAYER The soft sigh of the wind through the caverns almost seems to carry a secret message.
   ECHO OTHERS %n listens to the sounds eminating from the caverns.
ENDIF
;
IFPREVERB GAZE -1
   CLEARVERB
   ECHO PLAYER You glance around, catching sight of a flash of movement at the edge of the cavern.  
   ECHO OTHERS %n glances toward the back of the cavern.
ENDIF
;
IFPREVERB SIT -1
   CLEARVERB
   ECHO PLAYER You sit onto a slab of ebony stone like none you have ever seen.   
   ECHO OTHERS %n sits on a slab of ebony stone wincing at the chill.
   POSITION SIT
ENDIF
IFPREVERB LAY -1
   CLEARVERB
   ECHO PLAYER You stretch out on the dark floor.
   ECHO OTHERS %n stretches out on the dark floor.
   POSITION LAY
   APPEAR You notice a few stray bugs caught in %n's hair.
ENDIF

;Multiuse BOOK item. 
INUMBER 1186
NAME 384
WEIGHT 1
VOLUME 1
;
;--------------------<<<GM ITEM NOTE>>>----------------------------
;
;   If you add a story to the book, please add the itembit number and
;   description of the book to the gm note to assist others in the
;   future.
;
IFPREVERB EXAM -1
  IFVAR INTNUM3 = 1
    ECHO PLAYER This item is a generic book. It may be personalized for
    ECHO PLAYER events and/or rp purposes in fact for any darned thing
    ECHO PLAYER you please by altering the script.
    PLREVENT 1
    CONTPLREVENT
    ECHO PLAYER If ITEMBIT3 = 1  the book is The Journal of Donin Stonetooth.
    ECHO PLAYER used in the Scabbard Defender event series, January 1998.
    ECHO PLAYER If ITEMBIT1 = 1 the book is The Blessing of Defender.
    ECHO PLAYER If ITEMBIT2 = 1 the book is Invoices and Patterns.
  ENDIF
ENDIF
;
;------------------------------<<<NOTE>>>-------------------------------
;
;  ITEMVAL1 stores the page of the book. If ITEMVAL1 is 0, the book is
;  closed. The first page of the book is ITEMVAL1 = 1
;
IFPREVERB OPEN -1
  IFVAR ITEMVAL1 = 0
    CLEARVERB
     ECHO PLAYER You carefully open the book.
     ECHO OTHERS %n carefully opens the book.
     EQUAL ITEMVAL1 1
   ELSE
     ECHO PLAYER The book is already open.
   ENDIF
ENDIF
IFPREVERB CLOSE -1
  IFVAR ITEMVAL1 ! 0
    CLEARVERB
    ECHO PLAYER You carefully close the book.
    ECHO OTHERS %n carefully closes the book.
    EQUAL ITEMVAL1 0
   ELSE
     ECHO PLAYER The book is already closed.
   ENDIF
ENDIF
;
;------------------------<<<NOTE>>-----------------------
;
;The ITEMVAL1 counter runs from 0 to 8. One is added to the counter
;each time a player TURNS the book.
;
IFPREVERB TURN -1
  IFVAR ITEMVAL1 < 9
    IFVAR ITEMVAL1 > 0
      CLEARVERB
      ADD ITEMVAL1 1
      ECHO PLAYER You carefully turn the page.
      ECHO OTHERS %n carefully turns the page.
     ENDIF
   ENDIF
   IFVAR ITEMVAL1 > 8
    ECHO PLAYER You have reached the end of the book.
   ENDIF
   IFVAR ITEMVAL1 = 0
    ECHO PLAYER You have not yet opened the book.
   ENDIF
ENDIF
